# Tool Comparison

| Tool | What we could build with it | Strengths | Limitations | Suitable for our target audience? |
|------|------------------------------|------------|-------------|-----------------------------------|
| Scratch | Interactive cyber-safety game | Easy for beginners and fun for children | Limited advanced features | Yes |
| Canva | Storyboard and screen designs | Easy visual design | Not interactive | Yes |
| Visual Studio Code (VS Code) | Website or advanced cyber-safety game | Flexible, supports coding and teamwork | Requires coding knowledge | Yes |
| GitHub | Store and manage project files | Good for teamwork and version control | Can be confusing for beginners | Yes |

## Final Tool Choice
Our group selected Scratch and Canva as the main tools for the project. Scratch is suitable because it allows us to create an interactive cyber-safety game easily, while Canva helps us design attractive screens and storyboards. These tools are beginner-friendly, realistic for our timeframe, and suitable for our target audience.
